SIMPLE: symbolical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Symbolical
<hw>Sym*bol"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>symbolicus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>symboliko`s</grk>: cf. F. <ets>symbolique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to a symbol or symbols; of the nature of a symbol; exhibiting
or expressing by resemblance or signs; representative; <as>as, the
figure of an eye is <ex>symbolic</ex> of sight and knowledge</as>.</def>
-- <wordforms><wf>Sym*bol"ic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sym*bol"ic*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sacrament is a representation of Christ's death by such
<qex>symbolical</qex> actions as he himself appointed.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Symbolical delivery</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>the
delivery of property sold by delivering something else as a symbol,
token, or representative of it.</cd> <au>Bouvier. Chitty.</au> --
<col><b>Symbolical philosophy</b></col>, <cd>the philosophy expressed by
hieroglyphics.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1462 --></p>

<p><ent>Symbolics</ent>⟦br⟧
